Title: Unit trip due to failure of redundant IM152-1 / Update IM firmware
Analysis and Actions: The diagnostic buffer seems to show a loss of communication to the rack.It looks as though one module is lost and the other goes out 20-30 ms laterLatest firmware is 2.0.122.0.12 includes "Stability improvement for time stamping functionality after a redundancy switchover."2.0.9 includes "Stabilization of the communication between the redundant IM 152 modules in the case of external noise"2.0.7 includes "Stabilization of the redundancy communication between the two IMs 152"The error would also be explained by an error in the profibus connection or backplane.The IM modules were loaded with consistent firmware versions.The back plane and end plugs were replaced as these can also cause a rack failure

Assignees: AU REC Experts: Dino Cerillo. MY RREC Experts: Khoon Lon Sim
Title: Neerabup - BOP force point issue
Analysis and Actions: The forced result is OK if we forced from the source (10CPC01BB081 DI11_PV ‚Äì 12EKE30CP081||XG01HW)Created new BSMON without connection to IN1/2 (AFC708 ‚Äì BOP), forcing values at IN1/2, result is normal.Once IN1/2 is connected with any signal, force ‚Äútrue‚Äù at IN1/2, result is abnormal.Created new logic (assigned to AFC711), Copy the same logic to it.Force ‚Äútrue‚Äù at IN1, result is normal.We recommend should you be doing a reconnect RTC for AFC708 to do you risks assessments and do this during when you have more preparing on managing your BoP.
Further Actions: Since the abnormal behavior of forcing binary value is only happened in AFC708 (BOP).Suggested to disconnect and reconnect the runtime container AFC708.If the problem is not solved, then recommend resetting the BOP s7 CPU and offline download the program again on next outage.

Assignees: AU REC Experts: Cheng Cao. MY RREC Experts: Khoon Lon Sim
Title: SSA-968170 Remote Code Execution Vulnerability / Measures provided
Analysis and Actions: The development team is working in relation to this matter.As of now, some of the security recommendations that we can suggest are the following:- Restrict the access to the Application Highway, so that it is only allowed from the T3000 DMZ via T3000 Firewall- No bridging of an external network to either the Application or the Automation Highways- Use complex passwords, and change any passwords immediately, if they could have been exposed.There is a measure described to mitigate a part of the vulnerability. That measure requires a reboot of both servers.A possible attacker needs to be already at the application highway to use the vulnerability.Therefore, if above mentioned security recommendations are fulfilled there is no urgent need to do the steps, described in the updated announcement.We suggest that during the next opportunity and patch installation the steps can be done, this is sufficient.
Further Actions: Apply measures during the next patch update

Assignees: AU REC Experts: Abhilash Thalappan Kandoth
Title: FM logic online Engineering parameter change not possible
Analysis and Actions: Online parameter was unable able to change:-Trouble shooting performed :-Restarted WRA Master service & CFC container.Download/Compile performed for Rack 0 & 1 successfully.Container went to stop mode & all parameters shows BCE after Rack 1 FM downloaded.Power recycle of Rack 1 FM resolved the BCE issue.Online parameters change was working as per customer confirmation.‚ÄúError encountered while saving changed module parameters: Online parameter change failed withException Cannot set a parameter in the SIMATIC CFC in runtime container AS110_FM(810)!(Cannot set CFC Parameter for runtime container 810 because redundant value ca not be read!)‚ÄùRoot cause :-Analysis from logs, CFC parameter cannot set in FM due to redundancy was not responding fromRack 1.Trouble shooting performed :-Disconnect/reconnect the FM container,Compile/download performed using a spare FM card; but unsuccessful due to Spare FM washaving old firmware version.It was observed when we change the FM master to Rack 1 in T3000, all the values went to BCE.Conclusion: - FM Module and MMC are defective and require a replacement.Action performed:-A new MMC card was delivered to the site, and the spare FM module's firmware was updated toV2.1.3 to match the version of Rack 0.Instructions for downloading the FM module's & firmware upgrade were sent to customer.With a new FM module and a new MMC card on Rack 1, the customer was successfully able toadjust the parameters and initiate a download.
Extent?: Plant is in shutdown condition till 05-sep-23
Result: Parameters can be downloaded after replacement of FM module in Rack 1 with latest firmware V2.1.3  & new MMC card
What?: FM458 logic online Engineering parameter change not possible
